title: Grateful Dead Live at The Centrum on 1984-10-09
description:
Set 1

Dancin' In The Streets, Friend Of The Devil, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Althea, My Brother Esau, Big Railroad Blues, Let It Grow

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Jack Straw-> He's Gone-> Smokestack Lightning-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Throwing Stones-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: Revolution

reviews.review_text: It was good for me This was like my 16th or 18th show, don't recall much, the ornage building, the feeling of being in 11th grade, the feeling like people thought well he must be a loser deadhead, only to havethem trampling all of us down with their MTV In The dark nonsense a few months later, the Bobstack Lightning, which as a little deadhead bopper seemed so amazing. I guess it was, When one is 17 people who are 35 seem like they are 80, so that seemed like something significant, the way college seems important until u graduate and no one cares where u went t college. A gret show, looking back any shw with Big railroad Blues will do. I knew back then that I'd be going to 11/10/15 without jerry. It was so obvious, with my kaiser 99 sticker on my old turntable. Oh well, open that kaiser place, add cat tevens to ratdog, and let the CatDog shows begin, all in time for 2016 lection. If your also from Lexington write something here, and tell me why new england being shafted on the Dead and Company tour. NY is NOT Maine, at least it wasn't last time I looked at a map. Asking Heads from Maine to go to MSG is like asking people in Buffalo to go to Augusta maine.

Solid Show Interesting Jack Straw placement.
Highlights:  Slipknot!
